events.name: Golden State Warriors at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 36 points in three quarters and the Toronto Raptors routed the Golden State Warriors 130-77 Friday night, with the largest margin of victory in the NBA this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors rout Warriors 130-77 for 2nd win in last 15 games

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 26 points, Robert Williams had a career-high 20 points, nine rebounds and eight assists, and the Boston Celtics rolled to a 118-102 win over the Houston Rockets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Another perfect night by Williams lifts Celtics over Rockets

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 26 points and the Dallas Mavericks beat the New York Knicks 99-86 Friday night.
— Reserve guard Miles Bridges scored a season-high 23 points and the short-handed Charlotte Hornets overcame another injury and beat the Indiana Pacers 114-97 on Friday night.
— Jonas Valanciunas had 19 points and 11 rebounds, eight Grizzlies scored in double-figures and Memphis used a second-half burst for a 120-108 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Friday night.

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Bogdan Bodanovic scored 26 points, Kevin Huerter added 24 and five other Atlanta players scored in double figures as the short-handed Hawks beat the injury-slowed New Orleans Pelicans 126-103 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bodanovic scores 26 points, Hawks beat Pelicans 126-103

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 26 points and the Utah Jazz beat the Chicago Bulls 113-106 on Friday night for their 21st straight victory at home, a franchise record.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz beat Bulls for record 21st straight at home

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 32 points, Chris Paul had 17 points and 12 assists, and the Phoenix Suns built a 30-point lead by the end of the first quarter en route to a 140-103 victory over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns lead by 30 after 1 quarter, cruise past Thunder 140-103

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: Giannis Antetokounmpo had 47 points and 12 rebounds, and the Milwaukee Bucks snapped the Portland Trail Blazers' four-game winning streak with a 127-109 victory Friday night.

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 10 of his season-high 30 points in the fourth quarter and the short-handed Los Angeles Lakers thumped the Sacramento Kings 115-94 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma's season-high 30 points lead Lakers past Kings 115-94
